Ana Esther Hoffmann Mendizábal, also known as simply Anita Hoffmann (3 March 1919 – 11 October 2007), was a Mexican researcher, educator, academic, and biologist specializing in acarology and parasitology. She is a pioneer in the study of arachnids and acari in Mexico. She founded the Instituto Politécnico Nacional's Laboratory of Acrology in 1965, the first in Latin America, and another at the Faculty of Sciences of the National Autonomous University of Mexico in 1977.
